[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bayer 04 Leverkusen 2-0 Borussia Dortmund

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Borussia Dortmund missed the chance to move a point behind Bundesliga leaders Bayern Munich after losing at Bayer Leverkusen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Bayern were held 1-1 by Cologne earlier on Saturday, presenting Dortmund, who started the day three points behind, with the chance to cut the gap.
Admir Mehmedi headed Leverkusen ahead before former Manchester United striker Javier Hernandez doubled the lead.
Bayern are three points clear at the top of the table after six games.
Dortmund go into the international break four points behind the German champions, while Leverkusen climb to seventh.
Hernandez, 28, has five Bundesliga goals this season.
